{
  "esm": "0.6.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "coupled_refresh_regrid",
    "description": "Shared offline fixture for the cross-language REFRESH-PATH conformance (bead ess-14f.12 / RS-R4, parent ess-14f; CONFORMANCE_SPEC.md §5.10). A discretized, COUPLED, non-PDE model whose forcing is read from data loaders at a discrete cadence and REGRIDDED from the loader's native grid onto the simulation grid before it reaches the RHS. Two components over a 3-cell index i in [1,3]: `Box.c[i]` accumulates a loader-fed source scaled by a loaded factor (D(c[i]) = scale[i]*src[i]); `Sink.d[i]` integrates the coupled tracer across the component boundary (D(d[i]) = Box.c[i]). `src` is DISCRETE — its loader `emis` declares a `temporal` block, so it refreshes at the hourly cadence anchors; `scale` is CONST — its loader `factors` has no `temporal`, so it materializes once. BOTH loader fields are delivered on a COARSER 6-cell native grid and conservatively regridded (2:1 area-weighted coarsening) onto the 3-cell sim grid, so the refresh path exercises a genuine non-identity regrid kernel, not the identity pass-through. The forcing is piecewise-constant across the cadence segments, so the regridded arrays and the integrated trajectory are closed-form and checkable to solver tolerance — the analytic golden lives in golden/coupled_refresh_regrid.json. NOTE the two-view contract (RFC pure-io-data-loaders §4.6; mirrors tests/segmented_refresh_solve.rs): the loader-fed `src`/`scale` are declared `discrete`+`data_ingest` here so the cadence classifier resolves them CONST/DISCRETE, but the typed array-simulate compiler has no Discrete VariableType — a consumer STRIPS the loader-fed discrete declarations before compiling the RHS, where `src`/`scale` then resolve through the forcing buffer the regrid seam writes.",
    "authors": [
      "EarthSciSerialization/polecats/gastown.furiosa"
    ],
    "tags": [
      "refresh-path",
      "loader-seeded",
      "data-loader",
      "temporal",
      "discrete-variable",
      "regrid",
      "conservative",
      "cadence",
      "coupled",
      "conformance",
      "ess-14f.12"
    ]
  },
  "data_loaders": {
    "emis": {
      "kind": "grid",
      "source": {
        "url_template": "file:///data/emis/src_{date:%Y%m%d%H}.nc"
      },
      "temporal": {
        "frequency": "PT1H",
        "file_period": "P1D",
        "records_per_file": 24
      },
      "variables": {
        "src": {
          "file_variable": "surface_source",
          "units": "kg/s",
          "description": "Time-varying loader-fed source field, refreshed every hour as the loader advances to the next record. Its `temporal` block makes the loader output DISCRETE (RFC pure-io-data-loaders §4.6). Delivered on the coarse 6-cell native grid and conservatively regridded onto the 3-cell sim grid."
        }
      }
    },
    "factors": {
      "kind": "grid",
      "source": {
        "url_template": "file:///data/factors/scale.nc"
      },
      "variables": {
        "scale": {
          "file_variable": "scale_factor",
          "units": "1",
          "description": "Static per-cell scale factor. Its loader has NO `temporal` block, so the partition seeds it CONST (materialized once). Also delivered on the coarse 6-cell native grid and conservatively regridded onto the 3-cell sim grid."
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "models": {
    "Box": {
      "variables": {
        "c": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["i"],
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Integrated tracer concentration — CONTINUOUS cadence (changes every step). D(c[i]) = scale[i]*src[i]."
        },
        "src": {
          "type": "discrete",
          "shape": ["i"],
          "refresh": { "kind": "data_ingest", "source": "emis" },
          "description": "Loader-fed source read from the `emis` DataLoader (WITH temporal): DISCRETE cadence, refreshed at each hourly anchor. Resolves through the forcing buffer in the typed RHS after the loader-discrete strip; the regrid seam writes its regridded value there."
        },
        "scale": {
          "type": "discrete",
          "shape": ["i"],
          "refresh": { "kind": "data_ingest", "source": "factors" },
          "description": "Loader-fed scale factor read from the `factors` DataLoader (NO temporal): CONST cadence, materialized once. Resolves through the forcing buffer in the typed RHS after the loader-discrete strip."
        }
      },
      "equations": [
        {
          "_comment": "D(c[i]) = scale[i]*src[i]. scale is CONST (loader without temporal, materialized once); src is DISCRETE (loader with temporal, refreshed per anchor). Both are regridded from the 6-cell native grid onto i in [1,3]. Dense [1,3] ranges (not {from:<set>}) — index_sets are not yet carried through flatten (ess-14f.13).",
          "lhs": {
            "op": "arrayop",
            "args": [],
            "output_idx": ["i"],
            "ranges": { "i": [1, 3] },
            "expr": {
              "op": "D",
              "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["c", "i"] }],
              "wrt": "t"
            }
          },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "arrayop",
            "args": [],
            "output_idx": ["i"],
            "ranges": { "i": [1, 3] },
            "expr": {
              "op": "*",
              "args": [
                { "op": "index", "args": ["scale", "i"] },
                { "op": "index", "args": ["src", "i"] }
              ]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    "Sink": {
      "variables": {
        "d": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["i"],
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Integrated coupled tracer — CONTINUOUS. D(d[i]) = Box.c[i], a dotted cross-system reference the flatten namespacing carries through."
        }
      },
      "equations": [
        {
          "_comment": "D(d[i]) = Box.c[i]. The coupling: Sink integrates Box's state across the component boundary.",
          "lhs": {
            "op": "arrayop",
            "args": [],
            "output_idx": ["i"],
            "ranges": { "i": [1, 3] },
            "expr": {
              "op": "D",
              "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["d", "i"] }],
              "wrt": "t"
            }
          },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "arrayop",
            "args": [],
            "output_idx": ["i"],
            "ranges": { "i": [1, 3] },
            "expr": { "op": "index", "args": ["Box.c", "i"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
